rComments: Had Prof. Cooper for PSYC02 and PSYC36. He's no-nonsense, approachable, and committed to good teaching practices that help students build practical skills. He speaks very quickly in lectures but they're enjoyable and well put together. His assignments are fair and help students develop valuable, transferable communication and analytical skills.
A prof who genuinely cares about students and the material - definitely deserves to be on the sunshine list

This prof is incredible. He cares about what he teaches, he knows what he's talking about, he can properly/thoroughly explain concepts to students without overcomplicating it. Everyone can do very well in his classes by just showing up to his lectures and paying attention. Taking notes is necessary in order to study for his tests using his slides.

Had him in a super small class (less than 10 students) for stats so it gave him a lot of time to do some 1 on 1 work with us, which was much appreciated. the midterm was a bit on the harder side but the final had no tricks or surprises; everything that was on it was covered directly in lecture and just needed to be applied. 10/10 would do again

Take a course with him, especially if you plan on going to grad school; he will teach you exactly what you need to know and share some of his expertise. He is also extremely approachable, so if there is ever anything you don't understand, just talk to him. I probably would have left the course not understanding anything if I had a different prof.
